article.headline: UNC-Greensboro 68, Chattanooga 61
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Kyle Hines sank 18 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead UNC-Greensboro to a 68-61 win over Chattanooga on Saturday night. The Spartans (16-13, 12-6 Southern Conference) went on a 19-2 run in the opening minutes of the second half for their first double-digit lead of the night, 48-30, and led by as many as 19 points in the half. Mikko Koivisto scored 11 points for UNC-Greensboro and Ricky Hickman had 10. Casey Long led Chattanooga (14-17, 6-12) with 11 points and seven rebounds, and Ricky Hood added 10 points. The win was the first for the Spartans over the Mocs on their home floor since 2000. UNC-Greensboro enters the SoCon tournament on Thursday as the fourth seed facing No. 5 Furman. No. 8 Chattanooga will face ninth-seeded Elon.
